1
00:00:00,166 --> 00:00:01,432
(This drama complied with production
guidelines for filming child actors,)

2
00:00:01,433 --> 00:00:03,000
(and some scenes used
generative AI technology.)

3
00:00:03,000 --> 00:00:04,336
(Haemyeong University Hospital)

4
00:00:04,347 --> 00:00:05,660
(Episode 6)

5
00:00:49,782 --> 00:00:50,896
Mai.

6
00:00:50,920 --> 00:00:52,920
You're drooling.

7
00:00:53,650 --> 00:00:55,066
How much did all this cost?

8
00:00:55,909 --> 00:00:57,505
Even if you got a card...

9
00:00:58,442 --> 00:00:59,895
I'm a rich man's daughter.

10
00:00:59,930 --> 00:01:01,005
I can spend a little.

11
00:01:02,289 --> 00:01:05,669
Father might regret giving me that card.

12
00:01:07,242 --> 00:01:09,362
Let's keep this from mother for now.

13
00:01:09,387 --> 00:01:11,497
We shouldn't spend it so freely.

14
00:01:11,823 --> 00:01:14,946
He said to keep it a secret
until he leaves.

15
00:01:15,010 --> 00:01:16,023
It's just between us.

16
00:01:16,052 --> 00:01:17,419
Why do we need to keep this a secret?

17
00:01:17,549 --> 00:01:18,793
We don't need this.

18
00:01:18,919 --> 00:01:19,932
What?

19
00:01:19,964 --> 00:01:22,637
This isn't free. Think about it.

20
00:01:22,870 --> 00:01:27,957
Your mom raised two sons on her own
while caring for his parents.

21
00:01:28,383 --> 00:01:30,081
Even at 10,000 dollars a year,

22
00:01:30,082 --> 00:01:31,983
- that's 250,000.
- "Two hundred fifty thousand?"

23
00:01:32,008 --> 00:01:34,965
That's barely 800 dollars a month.

24
00:01:35,163 --> 00:01:37,006
We can't turn back time,

25
00:01:37,057 --> 00:01:39,520
but shouldn't he at least settle accounts
before leaving?

26
00:01:40,723 --> 00:01:43,353
I don't think this is right. Return it.

27
00:01:44,163 --> 00:01:46,170
I'll handle that.

28
00:01:46,450 --> 00:01:50,264
You go with Seung Woo
and talk to father properly.

29
00:01:50,541 --> 00:01:52,823
He really doesn't have much time left.

30
00:01:53,090 --> 00:01:55,487
- That soon?
- Yeah.

31
00:01:56,720 --> 00:01:57,773
And...

32
00:01:58,518 --> 00:02:01,780
he asked you to handle the funeral.

33
00:02:02,436 --> 00:02:04,648
He said not to leave
the two women alone...

34
00:02:04,649 --> 00:02:06,278
but to stay by their side.

35
00:02:06,462 --> 00:02:07,462
What?

36
00:02:08,269 --> 00:02:09,931
That's quite a request.

37
00:02:10,141 --> 00:02:11,847
He sees the three of you as siblings.

38
00:02:11,864 --> 00:02:13,492
That makes no sense.

39
00:02:13,555 --> 00:02:15,515
If Grandpa heard this,
he'd jump out of his grave.

40
00:02:15,540 --> 00:02:17,325
Think from his perspective.

41
00:02:17,350 --> 00:02:19,623
What doesn't make sense?
The three of you are siblings.

42
00:02:25,364 --> 00:02:28,528
One, two, three!

43
00:02:29,291 --> 00:02:31,896
- Happy to visit your grandparents' place?
- Yes!

44
00:02:31,930 --> 00:02:34,115
Someone's excited!

45
00:02:34,243 --> 00:02:36,798
If your grandpa were here,
he'd have come running out,

46
00:02:36,829 --> 00:02:39,690
but he's in Ho Chi Minh City right now.
Too bad, right?

47
00:02:39,715 --> 00:02:41,298
Yeah.

48
00:02:41,323 --> 00:02:43,852
Want to go get something good to eat?

49
00:02:44,016 --> 00:02:45,552
Yes, sounds good!

50
00:02:45,599 --> 00:02:46,712
- "Good?"
- Yes!

51
00:02:46,737 --> 00:02:49,012
Let's go!

52
00:02:55,363 --> 00:02:57,903
- Enjoy your meal.
- Thank you.

53
00:02:58,330 --> 00:03:00,042
Please enjoy your meal, Mother.

54
00:03:00,070 --> 00:03:03,210
You haven't been eating well lately.
You look worn out too.

55
00:03:03,484 --> 00:03:04,484
Thank you.

56
00:03:05,430 --> 00:03:07,419
I might get indigestion
from all this kindness.

57
00:03:07,450 --> 00:03:09,042
You ordered too much.

58
00:03:11,395 --> 00:03:13,897
Does your father run the place himself?

59
00:03:13,922 --> 00:03:15,466
I hear they get a lot of customers.

60
00:03:15,490 --> 00:03:17,498
My mom's really excited.

61
00:03:17,566 --> 00:03:18,970
I see.

62
00:03:19,043 --> 00:03:20,043
Mother,

63
00:03:22,033 --> 00:03:23,896
please stay strong.

64
00:03:26,470 --> 00:03:27,470
Okay.

65
00:03:27,980 --> 00:03:30,557
I'm ashamed to face you.

66
00:03:30,843 --> 00:03:33,716
You've suffered so much.

67
00:03:33,909 --> 00:03:37,095
I said I'd take good care of you,
and Seung Hyun said he was grateful.

68
00:03:37,303 --> 00:03:38,750
I'm grateful too.

69
00:03:39,810 --> 00:03:40,810
Then,

70
00:03:41,640 --> 00:03:44,756
since you're so grateful,
what if we moved here...

71
00:03:45,935 --> 00:03:49,082
This is a good neighborhood
for O Reum's kindergarten.

72
00:03:49,107 --> 00:03:51,249
You can get a place of your own.
I won't stop you.

73
00:03:51,251 --> 00:03:53,405
Seung Hyun won't agree.

74
00:03:53,635 --> 00:03:56,121
He says he can't live without you.
What an idiot.

75
00:03:56,230 --> 00:03:57,696
Did you just call my son an idiot?

76
00:03:57,720 --> 00:03:59,073
He's a mama's boy.

77
00:03:59,530 --> 00:04:01,225
You're just not persuasive enough.

78
00:04:01,250 --> 00:04:02,985
Convince him to move out with you.

79
00:04:03,010 --> 00:04:04,315
Why are you blaming me?

80
00:04:11,409 --> 00:04:13,699
Looks like you're coming down with a cold.

81
00:04:13,809 --> 00:04:17,979
Instead of mocking my son,
worry about your son's health.

82
00:04:22,576 --> 00:04:23,700
Seung Hyun was so thoughtful.

83
00:04:24,958 --> 00:04:26,640
Whenever I went to the supermarket,

84
00:04:27,317 --> 00:04:29,502
he'd secretly grab some soju...

85
00:04:30,145 --> 00:04:32,695
and slip it into my basket.

86
00:04:33,239 --> 00:04:34,239
Did you hear that?

87
00:04:34,562 --> 00:04:35,562
No.

88
00:04:37,930 --> 00:04:40,501
If father hadn't been there for me,

89
00:04:41,625 --> 00:04:43,194
I would've sent both my sons away...

90
00:04:43,684 --> 00:04:45,425
and given up on everything.

91
00:04:47,285 --> 00:04:49,114
After I put the kids to bed,

92
00:04:49,777 --> 00:04:52,294
I'd drink soju alone in the kitchen,

93
00:04:54,044 --> 00:04:56,377
and Mother would give me dirty looks.

94
00:04:58,785 --> 00:05:00,642
Seung Hyun must have noticed.

95
00:05:00,954 --> 00:05:02,967
He'd only just started school.

96
00:05:04,342 --> 00:05:06,105
Behind his grandmother's back,

97
00:05:06,950 --> 00:05:08,829
he'd pull up a chair and climb on it.

98
00:05:10,425 --> 00:05:12,004
With his little hands,

99
00:05:13,061 --> 00:05:15,061
he'd hide the soju...

100
00:05:15,685 --> 00:05:17,150
deep inside the refrigerator drawer.

101
00:05:17,496 --> 00:05:19,174
Seung Hyun did that?

102
00:05:19,278 --> 00:05:20,305
Yes.

103
00:05:20,330 --> 00:05:21,758
He did.

104
00:05:24,265 --> 00:05:28,534
That's when I pulled myself together.

105
00:05:31,627 --> 00:05:34,110
It's our children who make us mothers.

106
00:05:36,346 --> 00:05:37,691
Right, O Reum?

107
00:05:38,170 --> 00:05:42,639
You're what makes your mom a mother.

108
00:05:53,683 --> 00:05:55,299
Why do you keep doing this?

109
00:05:56,235 --> 00:05:57,402
Leave me alone.

110
00:05:57,516 --> 00:05:59,740
I won't need to dress up for a while.

111
00:06:02,407 --> 00:06:05,136
It's already been over two weeks.
Mom, you can't keep doing this.

112
00:06:05,161 --> 00:06:06,343
Your dad...

113
00:06:06,738 --> 00:06:08,489
could barely eat today.

114
00:06:10,113 --> 00:06:12,425
How could someone so full of life...

115
00:06:12,426 --> 00:06:14,992
fall apart so suddenly?

116
00:06:15,482 --> 00:06:17,692
I just can't believe it.

117
00:06:19,092 --> 00:06:21,644
Your dad is apologizing,

118
00:06:22,203 --> 00:06:24,791
and that boy still treats him like that.

119
00:06:25,050 --> 00:06:28,400
I'm so angry I can't contain myself.

120
00:06:28,590 --> 00:06:30,003
Is that what a son does?

121
00:06:30,130 --> 00:06:31,487
Dad made him this way.

122
00:06:31,489 --> 00:06:34,614
How can you say that
after seeing your dad beg on his knees?

123
00:06:36,872 --> 00:06:38,872
I'm angry at that boy too,

124
00:06:39,342 --> 00:06:41,479
but I'm angry at your dad as well.

125
00:06:42,123 --> 00:06:44,856
He's admitting you and me were mistakes.

126
00:06:45,536 --> 00:06:46,663
Why?

127
00:06:46,870 --> 00:06:48,476
Why does he have to do that?

128
00:06:48,783 --> 00:06:52,787
Look what he's done
to you and me all these years.

129
00:06:52,837 --> 00:06:54,667
And now he kneels again. Why?

130
00:06:54,692 --> 00:06:56,224
You chose him.

131
00:06:56,249 --> 00:06:58,742
- Na Ji Ni!
- You should've listened to Grandmother.

132
00:06:58,750 --> 00:07:00,631
You should've taken her advice!

133
00:07:04,073 --> 00:07:05,350
Stop drinking.

134
00:07:06,584 --> 00:07:07,584
Yeah.

135
00:07:08,143 --> 00:07:09,683
Anyone can point fingers at me,

136
00:07:11,799 --> 00:07:13,267
even my own mother,

137
00:07:14,163 --> 00:07:17,554
but not him.

138
00:07:18,090 --> 00:07:20,626
He can't do that to me.

139
00:07:21,048 --> 00:07:22,898
How could he kneel?

140
00:07:22,963 --> 00:07:24,579
Then what am I?

141
00:07:29,595 --> 00:07:32,195
Mom, think of it as dad apologizing.

142
00:07:32,590 --> 00:07:35,351
He wasn't saying you were a mistake.
It was dad's apology.

143
00:07:35,740 --> 00:07:39,517
He just wants to apologize to his son
as a father.

144
00:07:39,649 --> 00:07:40,802
Try to understand that.

145
00:07:41,056 --> 00:07:42,849
Mom, you love dad.

146
00:08:11,230 --> 00:08:14,220
He's fighting for his life right now.

147
00:08:14,762 --> 00:08:18,754
He's staying by our side,
enduring those painful IVs.

148
00:08:20,189 --> 00:08:21,503
But what is this?

149
00:08:21,920 --> 00:08:23,440
Is this love?

150
00:08:23,849 --> 00:08:27,394
Is this the love you'd risk your life for?

151
00:08:34,021 --> 00:08:35,828
This is all because of No Yeong Ju.

152
00:08:35,856 --> 00:08:36,876
Mom!

153
00:08:36,901 --> 00:08:40,756
I told her I'd let him see his sons
if she'd just complete the paperwork.

154
00:08:41,110 --> 00:08:44,150
I said either I could take them
or she could raise them.

155
00:08:44,474 --> 00:08:47,485
I told her I'd make everything easy
if she'd just sort out the paperwork.

156
00:08:47,534 --> 00:08:49,160
I gave in on everything.

157
00:08:49,363 --> 00:08:50,936
But in the end,

158
00:08:51,306 --> 00:08:55,263
she tore him away from his sons
and ruined our lives.

159
00:08:55,680 --> 00:08:57,805
Yeong Ju's stubbornness
caused all of this.

160
00:08:59,354 --> 00:09:02,834
Foolish. Unreasonable. Stubborn.

161
00:09:03,170 --> 00:09:04,790
What did she gain from all this?

162
00:09:04,815 --> 00:09:06,421
Everything's a mess now!

163
00:09:11,363 --> 00:09:13,028
Stop drinking and go inside.

164
00:09:21,828 --> 00:09:22,828
Mom.

165
00:09:23,271 --> 00:09:24,271
Are you okay?

166
00:09:24,303 --> 00:09:25,891
What am I going to do?

167
00:09:27,330 --> 00:09:30,064
What am I supposed to do
if your dad leaves us, Ji Ni?

168
00:09:30,816 --> 00:09:34,701
How am I supposed to live
after being treated so unfairly?

169
00:09:38,436 --> 00:09:43,169
Ji Ni, what am I going to do?

170
00:09:44,056 --> 00:09:47,150
What am I going to do?
I feel so sorry for him.

171
00:09:48,543 --> 00:09:54,081
He's suffered his whole life.
I feel so sorry for your dad.

172
00:09:54,715 --> 00:09:56,335
Go inside, Mom.

173
00:09:58,367 --> 00:10:01,352
Mom, dad will be okay.

174
00:10:01,838 --> 00:10:05,996
When you sober up, go to the hospital
and give him a hug.

175
00:10:07,059 --> 00:10:08,571
Go to him...

176
00:10:09,386 --> 00:10:13,313
and tell him he did well apologizing,
that you understand everything.

177
00:10:17,537 --> 00:10:19,411
- Let's go.
- Okay.

178
00:10:30,777 --> 00:10:31,878
What's this?

179
00:10:33,097 --> 00:10:35,319
I cleared out your dad's accounts.

180
00:10:36,810 --> 00:10:39,710
Mom, dad is still...

181
00:10:41,963 --> 00:10:43,308
Do you really have to go this far?

182
00:10:43,309 --> 00:10:47,191
Once he's gone,
I won't be able to touch this money.

183
00:10:47,193 --> 00:10:50,010
It's my money, and I still can't use it.

184
00:10:50,050 --> 00:10:52,511
That's the law.
That's what the documents say.

185
00:10:52,621 --> 00:10:54,495
That's why this feels so unfair.

186
00:10:56,073 --> 00:10:59,883
Do you know how hard it was
to withdraw all this with a debit card?

187
00:11:00,854 --> 00:11:02,354
No Yeong Ju...

188
00:11:02,473 --> 00:11:04,071
This is driving me crazy.

189
00:11:06,499 --> 00:11:08,015
It's driving me crazy!

190
00:11:12,726 --> 00:11:15,010
(Post Office)

191
00:11:16,614 --> 00:11:18,017
Your dad is here!

192
00:11:18,285 --> 00:11:19,606
Dad!

193
00:11:21,767 --> 00:11:23,594
O Reum, you're wearing new clothes.

194
00:11:24,246 --> 00:11:25,480
My husband.

195
00:11:27,093 --> 00:11:28,768
You look so pretty.

196
00:11:29,517 --> 00:11:31,348
What's with you?
You're suffocating O Reum.

197
00:11:31,350 --> 00:11:34,751
Your mom told me
how pretty you were as a child.

198
00:11:35,306 --> 00:11:36,540
Come on...

199
00:11:37,664 --> 00:11:38,973
Didn't you get scolded?

200
00:11:39,248 --> 00:11:41,762
About the department store card,
didn't she tell you anything?

201
00:11:42,096 --> 00:11:44,818
About that? I haven't told her yet.

202
00:11:45,017 --> 00:11:47,906
I just took her out for a meal.

203
00:11:47,908 --> 00:11:50,978
- I thought you went to tell her.
- No!

204
00:11:50,980 --> 00:11:52,651
Now's not the time.

205
00:11:52,653 --> 00:11:55,801
I should tell her
after the refund period is over.

206
00:11:55,802 --> 00:11:57,361
You've really thought this through.

207
00:11:58,103 --> 00:11:59,847
- What?
- Your plan's pretty meticulous.

208
00:11:59,849 --> 00:12:01,547
Of course.

209
00:12:01,743 --> 00:12:05,651
Father finally got to act
like a husband and a dad for once.

210
00:12:05,717 --> 00:12:08,262
As the eldest daughter-in-law,
I should support him perfectly.

211
00:12:08,263 --> 00:12:09,906
You're bold, I'll give you that.

212
00:12:11,783 --> 00:12:13,450
You should go. I have to work.

213
00:12:14,294 --> 00:12:16,583
O Reum's been having a runny nose,

214
00:12:16,584 --> 00:12:18,177
so I think we should take him
to the hospital tomorrow.

215
00:12:18,179 --> 00:12:19,616
The medicine's not working.

216
00:12:22,986 --> 00:12:24,631
They say even dogs
don't catch colds in summer,

217
00:12:24,633 --> 00:12:26,153
so what's with you, Cha O Reum?

218
00:12:27,827 --> 00:12:29,159
- Go on.
- Okay.

219
00:12:29,501 --> 00:12:30,501
Bye, Dad.

220
00:12:46,951 --> 00:12:49,227
Jung A, Ji Ni's coming.

221
00:12:50,567 --> 00:12:53,148
- I'll be right back.
- I don't believe you.

222
00:12:53,150 --> 00:12:54,928
Have a little faith.

223
00:12:55,328 --> 00:12:57,405
You always have to get the last word.

224
00:13:00,148 --> 00:13:01,799
Isn't that Do Hee?

225
00:13:06,317 --> 00:13:07,643
(Sunshine Class No. 2)

226
00:13:08,848 --> 00:13:10,000
Hello?

227
00:13:10,770 --> 00:13:11,770
Yeah.

228
00:13:13,677 --> 00:13:17,396
I'm a struggling small-business owner.

229
00:13:17,397 --> 00:13:19,147
Of course, I'm stuck here.

230
00:13:20,240 --> 00:13:23,042
I haven't been to Youth Street
in over a year.

231
00:13:23,064 --> 00:13:25,877
- Seriously, what kind of life is this?
- Geum Tae O.

232
00:13:25,983 --> 00:13:28,477
All you ever do is complain.

233
00:13:28,478 --> 00:13:29,929
It's practically your lifestyle now.

234
00:13:29,931 --> 00:13:33,064
- Have I really been that bad?
- Yes. I can't listen to it anymore.

235
00:13:34,690 --> 00:13:36,777
I'll come over later.
Freshen up and wait for me.

236
00:13:36,779 --> 00:13:40,010
Okay, got it. See you later. Bye.

237
00:13:44,499 --> 00:13:46,731
I'm sure this is Do Hee's account.

238
00:13:47,883 --> 00:13:49,196
How is this possible?

239
00:13:56,981 --> 00:13:58,648
How is your father doing?

240
00:14:03,857 --> 00:14:06,790
My poor friend.

241
00:14:10,870 --> 00:14:12,278
Why did you bring this?

242
00:14:12,313 --> 00:14:14,334
Dad loved this painting.

243
00:14:14,792 --> 00:14:16,100
He wants to keep it by his side.

244
00:14:16,101 --> 00:14:17,689
Has your mom been drinking all the time?

245
00:14:18,831 --> 00:14:20,884
She drinks
whenever she gets back from the hospital.

246
00:14:21,939 --> 00:14:24,517
I'm more concerned about mom.
She seems upset all the time.

247
00:14:24,540 --> 00:14:26,506
You really need to be good to her.

248
00:14:26,875 --> 00:14:28,214
That's what makes it hard.

249
00:14:29,037 --> 00:14:31,081
You know mom and I don't get along.

250
00:14:31,082 --> 00:14:33,189
That doesn't matter. She's your mother.

251
00:14:33,255 --> 00:14:34,672
Be good to her, no matter what.

252
00:14:35,355 --> 00:14:37,301
I haven't nagged you in a while...

253
00:14:39,598 --> 00:14:42,476
You're right.
I need you to keep me in line.

254
00:14:47,139 --> 00:14:49,039
But why does he like it?

255
00:14:49,040 --> 00:14:50,650
I like this painting too.

256
00:14:51,483 --> 00:14:53,373
I feel like I'm in it somewhere,

257
00:14:53,374 --> 00:14:56,414
and when I look for a happy face,

258
00:14:57,123 --> 00:15:00,267
every face reminds me of you.
They all look sad.

259
00:15:01,456 --> 00:15:04,178
That's right. Everyone has their own pain.

260
00:15:15,095 --> 00:15:17,003
- I'm leaving.
- Take care.

261
00:15:32,407 --> 00:15:34,958
(Director Im Ji Hu)

262
00:15:36,647 --> 00:15:37,647
Are you looking at it again?

263
00:15:38,766 --> 00:15:41,079
It's a beautiful painting.
I think of it sometimes too.

264
00:15:41,314 --> 00:15:44,296
- You feel that way too, Mr. Go?
- Yes, I don't believe the bullying rumor.

265
00:15:44,728 --> 00:15:46,756
No one who paints like this would do that.

266
00:15:47,294 --> 00:15:50,912
I heard it from the victim
and saw enough to believe it.

267
00:15:51,572 --> 00:15:53,643
If I only heard the rumor,
I wouldn't have believed it either.

268
00:15:53,644 --> 00:15:55,265
You saw it yourself? The incident?

269
00:16:12,911 --> 00:16:15,156
- Did Professor Bae write this?
- No.

270
00:16:16,109 --> 00:16:17,109
Yes.

271
00:16:18,048 --> 00:16:20,400
I wrote it, and Professor Bae approved it.

272
00:16:23,824 --> 00:16:26,788
A complete family, imperfections and all.

273
00:16:49,993 --> 00:16:52,939
An artist can't be so different
from their work.

274
00:17:02,162 --> 00:17:03,305
Excuse me...

275
00:17:04,959 --> 00:17:07,027
Dad is waiting for you.

276
00:17:07,288 --> 00:17:09,891
- Please go inside.
- Seeing you ruined my mood,

277
00:17:10,170 --> 00:17:11,733
so I don't want to go in anymore.

278
00:17:13,665 --> 00:17:15,207
Please don't be like that.

279
00:17:15,702 --> 00:17:17,047
Go see dad.

280
00:17:17,048 --> 00:17:20,188
Get your filthy hands off me. Let go.

281
00:17:24,405 --> 00:17:26,120
Please make sure you go in.

282
00:17:27,281 --> 00:17:28,797
I'm asking you.

283
00:17:40,920 --> 00:17:43,120
So you came here just because of that?

284
00:17:43,281 --> 00:17:45,387
If I go in feeling that way,

285
00:17:45,892 --> 00:17:49,201
- nothing good will come out of it.
- What did your little sister do wrong?

286
00:17:49,203 --> 00:17:51,296
It's not like she chose to be born.

287
00:17:52,330 --> 00:17:53,996
Don't call her my sister.

288
00:17:54,178 --> 00:17:56,041
If she hadn't been born,

289
00:17:57,128 --> 00:17:58,904
Dad would've come back home.

290
00:18:02,236 --> 00:18:04,443
I never even got to play
a simple game of soccer.

291
00:18:05,768 --> 00:18:07,065
That's right.

292
00:18:07,821 --> 00:18:11,614
That's right. Mi Joo's pretty good too.

293
00:18:11,696 --> 00:18:14,104
Hey, block him!

294
00:18:15,774 --> 00:18:18,470
Seung Woo, I scored!

295
00:18:18,538 --> 00:18:20,516
Yeah.

296
00:18:20,766 --> 00:18:22,507
One, zero. Hurry!

297
00:18:22,533 --> 00:18:24,846
While my friends ran around the field,

298
00:18:25,507 --> 00:18:27,426
I could only watch from the bench.

299
00:18:31,150 --> 00:18:32,447
That day,

300
00:18:33,722 --> 00:18:37,562
I regretted running after dad's car
more than I can say.

301
00:18:39,746 --> 00:18:41,494
Why did I care about that man?

302
00:18:42,130 --> 00:18:46,001
She was sitting in the back of the car,
watching me.

303
00:18:46,071 --> 00:18:49,420
Watching me run after the moving car.

304
00:18:53,830 --> 00:18:55,313
I'll never forget it.

305
00:19:00,718 --> 00:19:03,825
Is it too cliché? Should I stop?

306
00:19:04,996 --> 00:19:07,619
I feel like I can see young Seung Woo.

307
00:19:11,845 --> 00:19:14,571
What are you doing after work?
Want to go to Yangpyeong?

308
00:19:14,879 --> 00:19:17,364
Because you feel sorry for me? Pity me?

309
00:19:17,365 --> 00:19:18,702
Anyway,

310
00:19:18,790 --> 00:19:21,590
you really know how to say sweet things.

311
00:19:21,757 --> 00:19:24,779
"Pity?" It's love.

312
00:19:25,780 --> 00:19:27,125
Sorry.

313
00:19:27,213 --> 00:19:32,040
But I might have to go to the hospital
with Seung Hyun tonight.

314
00:19:32,148 --> 00:19:35,171
Ever since that day,
he's been hanging by a thread.

315
00:19:35,172 --> 00:19:36,982
He keeps calling people over
at the slightest thing.

316
00:19:39,430 --> 00:19:40,860
I should get going.

317
00:19:49,990 --> 00:19:53,013
Thanks for listening to me vent.

318
00:19:53,790 --> 00:19:55,631
My pleasure.

319
00:19:59,566 --> 00:20:02,937
After meeting you,
I started to understand dad,

320
00:20:04,137 --> 00:20:06,218
just a little.

321
00:20:06,220 --> 00:20:07,403
If I had met you...

322
00:20:07,995 --> 00:20:12,101
after I was already married,

323
00:20:12,479 --> 00:20:14,245
would I have become a cheater too?

324
00:20:14,894 --> 00:20:17,453
Is there really such a thing
as the right timing for love?

325
00:20:17,759 --> 00:20:20,434
The right timing for love...

326
00:20:21,796 --> 00:20:24,886
I guess I helped you make up
with your dad a little.

327
00:20:24,888 --> 00:20:26,353
You helped a lot.

328
00:20:27,602 --> 00:20:30,296
Ji Hu, is something wrong?

329
00:20:30,865 --> 00:20:32,523
You seem angry.

330
00:20:40,356 --> 00:20:41,644
What is this?

331
00:20:41,679 --> 00:20:42,889
Why?

332
00:20:43,810 --> 00:20:46,375
- How did you see this?
- It's a public account.

333
00:20:46,690 --> 00:20:48,075
Anyone can see it.

334
00:20:48,076 --> 00:20:50,594
Didn't you post it
so anyone could see it and DM you?

335
00:20:51,776 --> 00:20:53,969
- Right.
- "Right?"

336
00:20:54,390 --> 00:20:56,583
Do Hee, aren't we dating?

337
00:20:56,738 --> 00:20:57,946
Or were we just friends?

338
00:20:58,000 --> 00:21:00,290
We said we'd introduce our families
when your parents return.

339
00:21:00,291 --> 00:21:03,860
- Didn't we?
- I know. We did.

340
00:21:03,999 --> 00:21:05,458
This is just for fun.

341
00:21:05,826 --> 00:21:09,366
I don't need to start acting
like a married woman already.

342
00:21:10,849 --> 00:21:13,891
- "Acting like a married woman?"
- There you go again.

343
00:21:14,208 --> 00:21:15,500
You're being too serious.

344
00:21:15,522 --> 00:21:18,748
Have I ever neglected you
because of this? I haven't, right?

345
00:21:19,416 --> 00:21:20,803
It's just...

346
00:21:20,958 --> 00:21:22,333
a little ego boost.

347
00:21:22,375 --> 00:21:24,541
I just want to know
I can still get this kind of attention.

348
00:21:24,583 --> 00:21:26,690
Why do you even need that?

349
00:21:26,692 --> 00:21:28,123
Being with me should be enough.

350
00:21:28,208 --> 00:21:30,208
Why seek validation from other men?

351
00:21:30,250 --> 00:21:31,458
Everyone does it.

352
00:21:31,625 --> 00:21:34,783
Just to check, "Am I still pretty?"

353
00:21:34,958 --> 00:21:37,825
- Still...
- Checking if you still get lots of DMs?

354
00:21:41,440 --> 00:21:43,204
When we decided to be together,

355
00:21:43,741 --> 00:21:45,295
I had one request.

356
00:21:45,466 --> 00:21:46,882
Focus on me.

357
00:21:47,096 --> 00:21:48,697
And don't lie to each other.

358
00:21:49,627 --> 00:21:50,944
It may sound obvious,

359
00:21:50,969 --> 00:21:52,291
but I specifically brought it up...

360
00:21:54,375 --> 00:21:56,355
because I've been hurt before.

361
00:21:56,625 --> 00:21:59,728
I know. I was just bored.

362
00:22:00,191 --> 00:22:02,225
That's all. No other reason.

363
00:22:02,291 --> 00:22:03,916
You've been busy with the center,

364
00:22:04,208 --> 00:22:06,112
and I've been preparing
for the exhibition.

365
00:22:06,551 --> 00:22:09,708
You know painting doesn't always go well.

366
00:22:11,000 --> 00:22:13,713
So when I'm stuck,
it's just something to pass the time.

367
00:22:14,197 --> 00:22:15,197
Don't you get it?

368
00:22:15,541 --> 00:22:17,494
It means nothing. Just killing time.

369
00:22:18,640 --> 00:22:21,044
I've never met anyone from my DMs.

370
00:22:21,166 --> 00:22:22,375
I'm telling the truth.

371
00:22:22,750 --> 00:22:23,750
Okay?

372
00:22:25,833 --> 00:22:27,515
Ji Hu.

373
00:22:30,916 --> 00:22:32,040
Let's talk again later.

374
00:22:32,041 --> 00:22:33,291
Ji Hu.

375
00:22:34,588 --> 00:22:35,879
I'll call you.

376
00:22:38,244 --> 00:22:39,452
Ji Hu!

377
00:22:40,666 --> 00:22:41,896
Please move!

378
00:22:42,833 --> 00:22:44,208
Please move!

379
00:22:50,583 --> 00:22:51,791
Father!

380
00:22:52,235 --> 00:22:53,402
Wait a moment.

381
00:22:54,000 --> 00:22:55,500
What's wrong with him?

382
00:22:55,708 --> 00:22:56,916
Is he in critical condition?

383
00:22:56,958 --> 00:22:58,033
Are you a family member?

384
00:22:58,375 --> 00:22:59,600
- Yes.
- Call the family right away.

385
00:22:59,611 --> 00:23:01,874
I was just about to call them.

386
00:23:01,875 --> 00:23:03,041
Please hurry.

387
00:23:31,166 --> 00:23:33,624
Does an autumn song cool you down
in summer?

388
00:23:33,625 --> 00:23:34,833
It makes me sad.

389
00:23:34,916 --> 00:23:36,715
It brings back memories of my first love.

390
00:23:40,958 --> 00:23:42,250
What were you thinking?

391
00:23:43,335 --> 00:23:47,414
I was thinking, "Thank goodness
I sang it without making any mistakes."

392
00:23:48,375 --> 00:23:50,875
Do you really think you sang it
without making any mistakes?

393
00:23:50,958 --> 00:23:52,125
Unbelievable.

394
00:23:54,458 --> 00:23:55,666
Did I make a mistake?

395
00:23:55,875 --> 00:23:57,041
You did well.

396
00:23:58,625 --> 00:24:00,458
That's all for today.

397
00:24:00,844 --> 00:24:02,242
Goodbye, everyone.

398
00:24:02,666 --> 00:24:03,981
Goodbye.

399
00:24:06,208 --> 00:24:07,416
(My Daughter-in-Law)

400
00:24:09,000 --> 00:24:11,728
It's me. How's O Reum?

401
00:24:14,176 --> 00:24:15,176
What?

402
00:24:15,584 --> 00:24:17,766
I don't have their number.

403
00:24:18,621 --> 00:24:21,618
Okay. I'll be right there.

404
00:24:24,496 --> 00:24:25,939
You can leave that here.

405
00:24:25,940 --> 00:24:27,816
I'll take care of it.
Is there an emergency?

406
00:24:27,838 --> 00:24:30,833
Yes. Please take care of it.

407
00:25:00,154 --> 00:25:01,719
Did they take my father for tests?

408
00:25:01,752 --> 00:25:04,352
Why are you so late?
Your father is in critical condition.

409
00:25:04,374 --> 00:25:05,663
Hurry to the ICU.

410
00:25:05,746 --> 00:25:06,746
Okay.

411
00:25:23,132 --> 00:25:24,299
Yeong Ju.

412
00:25:37,431 --> 00:25:39,153
I'm sorry.

413
00:25:40,032 --> 00:25:41,773
I've put you through so much.

414
00:25:44,083 --> 00:25:45,946
Don't talk like that.

415
00:25:47,001 --> 00:25:48,579
You need to stay strong.

416
00:25:51,583 --> 00:25:52,971
Father,

417
00:25:53,516 --> 00:25:54,835
I'm sorry.

418
00:25:55,747 --> 00:25:57,333
I was wrong.

419
00:26:03,580 --> 00:26:05,316
Don't do this.

420
00:26:31,904 --> 00:26:33,621
I'm sorry too.

421
00:26:44,891 --> 00:26:46,222
Dad.

422
00:26:47,304 --> 00:26:50,013
Dad.

423
00:26:50,125 --> 00:26:55,629
Dad, no!

424
00:26:55,662 --> 00:26:57,985
No!

425
00:27:07,041 --> 00:27:09,744
Doctor, please help my dad!

426
00:27:09,788 --> 00:27:10,788
Okay?

427
00:27:11,375 --> 00:27:14,354
The patient declined life-sustaining care.

428
00:27:22,833 --> 00:27:26,905
- Dad.
- July 13, 2026, 5:52 p.m.

429
00:27:26,958 --> 00:27:28,125
Patient Cha Min Ki...

430
00:27:29,125 --> 00:27:30,541
has passed away.

431
00:27:33,521 --> 00:27:35,125
Dad.

432
00:27:45,775 --> 00:27:47,611
Dad.

433
00:27:50,297 --> 00:27:54,172
Dad, no!

434
00:28:19,875 --> 00:28:23,207
(Family Register)

435
00:28:23,208 --> 00:28:24,535
I admitted it.

436
00:28:24,558 --> 00:28:27,082
Yeong Ju, is this why you've been coming
to the hospital all this time?

437
00:28:27,083 --> 00:28:29,207
Did you really have to do this?
This is humiliating.

438
00:28:29,208 --> 00:28:30,499
For the first time, I understand...

439
00:28:30,500 --> 00:28:33,540
the petty urge to expose them
as the ones who had the affair.

440
00:28:33,541 --> 00:28:36,291
Neither of you is related to this man.

441
00:28:36,293 --> 00:28:38,833
I didn't ask to be born, so please stop.

442
00:28:38,875 --> 00:28:40,560
Those damn papers!

443
00:28:40,571 --> 00:28:42,840
I really hate you, Dad.

444
00:28:43,319 --> 00:28:44,917
It's over now.

445
00:28:46,174 --> 00:28:48,174
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
